<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="542" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d542">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">125.61383/120: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-24T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            24, 1919, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>2259. Your 3230, October 21, 5 p.m.</p>
                            <p>You will insist that Mexican Government inform you definitely what
                                steps have been taken to effect release of Jenkins, and inform <pb facs="0664" n="579" xml:id="pg_579"/> Foreign Office that this
                                Government expects Mexican Government to take effective steps to
                                obtain his release unharmed even if payment by Mexico of indemnity
                                demanded be necessary.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>